Since 1983 Apple has told told developers not just emulate a text console on Mac, use the native UI. Similarly Apple's App Store requirements have prohibited general purpose OS emulation, SDKs, etc that would allow on board programming and a different UI experience.<br> <br>

There's nothing new here. There is no real confusion over what i<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
